title: Replies to initial written questions raised by Finance Committee Members in examining the Estimates of Expenditure 2011-12
question_text: Regarding scrutinising and executing Deeds of Mutual Covenant, assignments and related documents in respect of Government, Institution and Community accommodation in private developments, please advise the number of Deeds of Mutual Covenant and sub-Deeds of Mutual Covenant that were under negotiation at the start of 2010-11, the number that were agreed during the year, and the number that were under negotiation at the end of the year. Please describe the establishment involved in this work, and advise whether any directorate grade officer is involved in such work on a full-time basis. Please advise how many of the current establishment have been engaged in this work for five or more years.
reply_text: The Agency had 23 Deeds of Mutual Covenant (DMCs)/sub-DMCs for scrutiny at the beginning of 2010-11 and has completed the scrutiny of 21 DMCs/sub-DMCs this financial year. At present, the Agency is scrutinising four DMCs/sub-DMCs. The Agency deploys two solicitor grade officers (one senior solicitor and one solicitor) and two Land Conveyancing Officers for the scrutiny and execution of DMCs/sub-DMCs, assignments and related legal documents in respect of Government, Institution and Community accommodation in private developments in addition to their other duties. Additionally, Housing Department deployed a solicitor to the Agency from 2007 to 2010 to cope with the additional demand of DMC scrutiny arising from Housing Authority’s Divestment project. No directorate officer is involved in the above work. The Agency has been deploying the above establishment on such duties for over five years. Signature Name in block letters K K Kwok Post Title Government Property Administrator Date 17.3.2011
